The Independent Corrupt Practices and Other Related Offences Commission says it is yet to co conclude investigations on billions of naira and cars seized in a house in Abuja.

There had been reports that the house  belonged to former Chief of Army Staff Lt. Gen. Tukur Buratai Rtd.

But in a statement by its spokesman Azuka Ogugua on Friday, the ICPC facts available for the time being indicates that the property is owned by owner of K Salam Construction Company, a military contractor.

“The attention of the Independent Corrupt Practices and Other Related Offences Commission (ICPC) has been drawn to some inaccurate and concocted reports in the media about the seizure of multibillion-naira cash, dollars, Rolex watches stockpiled in an Abuja property.

“The Commission wishes to state that ICPC operatives raided a property in Wuse 2 of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abuja, on Thursday, 16th June, 2022 between 5:00pm and 12:00am in suspicion of money laundering . Facts available for the time being indicates that the property is owned by owner of K Salam Construction Company, a military contractor.

“The Commission recovered money and other items from the property viz. N175,706,500; $220,965; G-Wagon; 2022 editions of BMW and Mercedes Benz cars; customized mobile phones; several designer wrist watches, including three Rolexes, and some property documents.

Former Chief of Army Staff, Lt. General Tukur Buratai, on Friday, denied having a home in Wuse, or bulletproof cars, contrary to reports that his home was, raided by the operatives of the Independent Corrupt Practices and Other Related Offences Commission (ICPC).⁣
⁣
Buratai, in a statement, by its Legal Advisor, Barr. Osuagwu Ugochukwu, described the reports as a smear and fabricated tales, published to tarnish his image.⁣
⁣
An online media, ‘Not The Guardian’ published a story – ‘Exclusive: Anti-graft Agency, ICPC Uncovers Billions In Cash Meant For Arms, Ammunition To Fight Boko Haram In Abuja Home Of Ex-Chief Of Army Staff, Buratai,’ – reported that N1.85 billion, was recovered from the retired army general’s house when the ICPC raided his home.⁣
⁣
The statement reads in part: “My attention has been drawn to a recent publication on the webpage of Sahara reporters titled, ‘Exclusive: Anti-graft Agency, ICPC Uncovers Billions In Cash Meant For Arms, Ammunition To Fight Boko Haram In Abuja Home Of Ex-Chief Of Army Staff, Buratai’ which was published on June 6, 2022.⁣
⁣
“I have gone through the said publication and have interfaced with Ambassador T.Y. Buratai and can authoritatively say the content of the publication is false, concocted and malicious.⁣
⁣

HORREUR et TRISTESSE

Mais où va ce monde ?  Comment peut on être arrivé là ! 
.
Quand aurons nous le courage de  combattre et défendre nos enfants, les femmes, la nature...

Quand cesserons nous d'accepter qu'une minorité richissime décide de nos vies....

J'ai avorté deux fois... car mon corps ne supportait aucune contraception...qu'il a fallu que je supplie pour être ligaturee à 37ans...et que le jour de l'intervention alors que j'avais été anesthésiee le chirurgien ne voulait plus me ligaturer car je n'avais pas signer la 3ème page de la  décharge...

Comment peut-on on accepter de vivre dans une société qui a masque des enfants, qui pollue et détruit la faune, qui dispose du corps des femmes...

On m'a souvent dit ces derniers mois que j'étais extrémiste quand je parlais de dictature dans ce monde.... me balançant que la Syrie c'était ça une dictature....alors voilà rassurons nous les États Unis sont un pays développé, avec un suffrage universel....des américains et américaines qui ont pris le temps d'aller s'exprimer pour qu'une cours suprême leur mette dans le c.... 

77% des américains sont pour le droit à l'avortement...

Alors continuons de croire que tout va bien.... et fermons bien nos yeux sur tout.... pour ne pas à avoir à oser prendre notre courage en main et LUTTER.....

SHAME....Honte....pourrons-nous regarder en face nos enfants dans quelques années ...je pleure...je saigne ce sang de lune....qui m'appartient et dont jamais personne ne disposera pour moi.....

It takes great courage to invite foreign journos to visit a protest site! What began as a protest on April 9 at the Galle Face Green in Colombo against the corrupt activities of politicians that had caused an unprecedented economic crisis, has now turned into a permanent protest village called GotaGoGama. It’s a call for removal of President Gotabaya and the Rajapaksa regime (Gota Go, gama means village). The camp site near the Secretariat is a well-organised battlefield with peaceful protests that draws Sri Lankans from all walks of life - Buddhist monks, Muslim traders, students, teachers, lawyers, army veterans, amputees and concerned citizens. There’s a legal aid tent, a library, an artists’ tent and a people’s university! Volunteers hand out free food and water, others hold placards or wave the Sri Lankan flag, some scrawl messages and interesting posters line the walls with one singular message - Go Home Gota. Also spotted a Fearless artwork by @shiloshivsuleman! Similar GotaGoGama protest camps have now come up in other cities like Kandy and Galle. Call it Sri Lanka’s Arab Spring. I guess when you gotta go, you Gota go!

Rampart (2011) Dir. Oren Moverman 

Synopsis: Follows veteran police officer Dave Brown, the last of the renegade cops, as he struggles to take care of his family, and fights for his own survival.

I've talked before about the construct of "copaganda" in films and especially network television. Those programs brainwash the American public into believing that the police are meant to keep the community safe, when time and time again, they have proven the opposite. Many join the police force thinking they'll be an exception to the rule. They'll be the heroes who makes a meaningful change in the system - a self-righteous delusion. Others know it can't be saved, and they join instead to be the gunslinger of the community, embracing the corruption.

Dave Brown falls into the latter of those two. A Vietnam vet turned wannabe John Wayne, his character is a nihilistic cowboy who views all life - including his own - as dispensable. I'll be honest, I can only think of a few other films or shows that are as pessimistic about law enforcement as this film ("The Wire" comes to mind). This is an incredibly bitter film. I can see this pessimism being too much for most audiences, which would explain such low audience ratings on Rotten Tomatoes.

One of the script's biggest strengths is that it never seeks to explain to us why Brown is as bad as he is. Dave Brown is one the most morally bankrupt cops I have ever seen on screen, rivaled only by Alonzo Harris. At no point do we get a monologue from Harrelson explaining his childhood or why he is a murderous, bigoted, shallow man with such a profound lack of insight. I loved that this film had the maturity and respect for the audience to not include that.

The film is somewhat misleading in the sense that this isn't based on true events. The Rampart district in L.A. in the late 1990s was an absolute cesspool of corruption, but the character of Dave Brown isn't a real person, but rather a personification of all of the worst that comes to mind when you think of law enforcement in the United States. It's an unrelentingly grim experience, but equally as enlightening.

Nach einer kurzen Pause hier auf Social Media melden wir uns jetzt mit umso mehr Veranstaltungen zurück!

Den Start macht morgen (25.06.) der Christopher Street Day in Tübingen. Um 13:30 trifft sich unsere JEF Laufgruppe am Keplergymnasium - falls ihr spontan noch Lust bekommen habt mitzulaufen schreibt uns am besten damit wir uns finden!

Am Dienstag nächste Woche (28.06.) findet unsere Sitzung am IfP statt. Eingeladen ist Alice Dorison, die über die französischen Parlamentswahlen sprechen wird. Mehr Details folgen in einem eigenen Post am Wochenende.

Am Mittwoch (29.06.) gibt es gleich die doppelte Ladung Europa. Um 19 Uhr beginnt die Zoom-Veranstaltung der JEF Freiburg zum Thema Korruption im internationalen Waffenhandel. Eingeladen sind dazu Gäst:innen von Corruption Tracker. Anmelden könnt ihr euch über den QR Code auf der slide im Post oben oder per Nachricht an die JEF-Freiburg.

Ebenfalls um 19 Uhr startet die Online Diskussion der Landes AG Empowerment und Diversity zum Thema „Recht auf Abtreibung, kostenloser Zugang zu Verhütungsmitteln, Kampf um Selbstbestimmung?! - Reproduktive Rechte von Frauen im europäischen Vergleich“ auf Webex. Eingeladen als Gästinnen sind Maria Noichl (MdEP), Sarah Diehl (Publizistin) und eine Vertreterin von Doctors for Choice. Für die Zugangsdaten schreibt einfach eine kurze mail an manuel.glattbach@jef-bw.de oder an sophia.leiendecker@jef-bw.de .

Last but not least gibt es nächsten Freitag (01.07.) noch eine zweite Veranstaltung zur französischen Ratspräsidentschaft. Die Konrad Adenauer Stiftung, das Institut Culturel Franco-Allemand und das Institut für Politikwissenschaft Tübingen geben gemeinsam einen Rückblick über die vergangenen 6 Monate. Eingeladen sind Christina Bellmann von der KAS und Florian Ziegenbalg von der Europa-Union Baden-Württemberg. Moderiert wird die Debatte von Prof. Dr. Gabriele Abels. Das ICFA bittet um eine vorherige Anmeldung unter info@icfa-tuebingen.de .

It also disclosed that the Managing Director of K Salam Construction Company Nigeria Limited, Kabiru Sallau, was arrested and that investigations are ongoing. Nigeria’s Independent Corrupt Practices and Other Related Offences Commission (ICPC) has described as inaccurate reports about a raid by its operatives on an Abuja property allegedly belonging to former Chief of Army Staff, Tukur Buratai. 

In a statement issued on Friday, the ICPC stated that the reports about the retired general were concocted.

“The attention of the ICPC has been drawn to some inaccurate and concocted reports in the media about the seizure of multibillion-naira cash, dollars, Rolex watches stockpiled in an Abuja property,” read the statement in part.

“The Commission wishes to state that ICPC operatives raided a property in Wuse 2 of the FCT, Abuja, on Thursday, 16th June, 2022 between 5:00pm and 12:00am in suspicion of money laundering. Facts available for the time being indicate that the property is owned by owner of K Salam Construction Company, a military contractor.”

The statement further disclosed that the ICPC recovered ₦175,706,500, $220,965, a Mercedes-Benz G-Wagon, a Mercedes-Benz car, a BMW, customized mobile phones, several designer wrist watches, and some property documents.

It also disclosed that the Managing Director of K Salam Construction Company Nigeria Limited, Kabiru Sallau, was arrested and that investigations are ongoing.

.⁠
He discusses how many EU countries, including France, do not want to put the deepening process of the Union in jeopardy by a premature process of enlargement that would see an unfit, corrupt and divided Ukraine join the European community. In this context, Shea supports the presentation of a candidate status under conditions or a reverse clause allowing the Union to slow the process down if required. ●N1.85 billion recovered from General Burutai's home.

About N1.85 billion in cash has been recovered from a house and office in Abuja said to belong to former Chief of Army Staff, Lt. General Tukur Buratai.

Buratai, a retired Lieutenant General was the COAS between 2015 and 2021 and is at present Nigerian ambassador in Benin.

According to the report, ICPC officials stormed the house in the Wuse area, beside the National Open University of Nigeria Campus in Abuja last week after it received a tip-off from a whistleblower.

The huge cash was part of the money earmarked for the purchase of arms and ammunition by the Muhammadu Buhari-led government.

Last week Thursday, ICPC officials stormed a house in Wuse area of Abuja, beside National Open University and arrested a man, Kabiru Salisu after they saw N850 million cash in the house,” a source told SaharaReporters.

He claimed the money belonged to Tukur Buratai who was in Cotonou at that time. Officials of the ICPC took him to an office where another N1billion in cash was also discovered. Also, bulletproof cars, BMW, G-Wagon worth N450m were recovered.

Serious pressure is being mounted to claim money found was only N30m,” another source said.

Posted @withregram • @fringehealthtv 'Moderna Wants You To Pay Its Legal Bills'

'Every day, Americans access drugs, medical devices, and other health products sold by private companies but subsidized by the US government through its various agencies, from Medicare to the Veterans Administration. The firms are handsomely rewarded for the trouble, winning guaranteed-purchase contracts and, sometimes, grants to research their products in the first place.'

'But for one company, scoring on both ends of the process in this way hasn’t been enough. Not only did it benefit from massive government grants, and not only did it realize super-profits on a product many of us were required to take, the company now wants taxpayers to foot the bill for the alleged patent infringement involved in the making of that product. The company’s name is Moderna, and the product in question is the Spikevax Covid vaccine.'

'In a little-noticed court filing last month, Moderna invoked a World War I-era statute to shield itself from liability for allegedly borrowing, without pay, a vaccine-delivery system pioneered by other researchers. If this is allowed, it will set a new low in the legalized corporate looting of the public fisc.'

'In 2019, Moderna was an obscure biotech firm in Cambridge, Mass., with a “long-unrealized dream of using the technique of mRNA insertion to create new drugs,” as the Boston Globe put it. That’s a gentle way of saying the company was a dud. Up to that point, it had never brought to market a single pharmaceutical. Today, Moderna is a $50 billion behemoth with contracts around the world, whose CEO earned more than $18 million in compensation last year alone.'

Written by Sohrab Ahmari

Absolutely incredible. We Own This City is the best miniseries I have ever seen. Easily the best show in the last four years. David Simon, George Pelecanos, and Reinaldo Marcus have created another look into the systemic failures of policing in Baltimore and how group of rouge cops can terrorize a city with near immunity.  @jonnybernthal portrayal of Wayne Jenkins, innocent rookie to one cop without a moral compass is one for the ages.

What makes “We Own This City” work is how it shows the culture of the Baltimore police department and how they produced a Wayne Jenkins and his counterparts. These are not “One bad apple” but an entire department that lets cops behave as if accountability does not exist. Watching the show, you can see how Wayne Jenkins was able to grow into who he was.

The great @officialspikelee once said “Write what you know” and I think that is what makes “We Own This City” so effective. Simon has been writing about Baltimore for years. He has an intimate feel for the city and it shows in the story. Also, the show is adapted directly from @justin_fenton sensational book of the same name. The language, accents, and the way the people move and act is so Baltimore. It must be noted that @dwatkinsworld, writer and Baltimore resident was in the writers room for this, so the little nuances that Black
Baltimore has is represented well (Also, check out D’s We Own This City Podcast - dope and heartbreaking all at the same time). There is humor - I loved @happydaggy line “I flaut” and heartbreak - @jamiehector Sean Suitter was on my mind for days.

In all, We Own This City is essential viewing. Great great stuff. #hbo #weownthiscity #writing #baltimore #police #america #tv #crime #corruption #love

It’s known as “negative immunity.” 

According to a study published in the New England Journal of Medicine, individuals who received two doses of the Pfizer and Moderna vaccine but had no previous infection were found with negative immunity against both Omicron subvariants, indicating a greater risk of contracting COVID-19 than an unvaccinated person.

Over six months after getting two doses of the Pfizer vaccine, immunity against any Omicron infection dropped into the negative (-3.4%), meaning it actually increased the chances of contracting infection. 

But for two doses of the Moderna vaccine, immunity against any Omicron infection dropped further into the negative (-10.3%) after more than six months passed after the last injection.

A previous infection without vaccination offers around 50 percent immunity. 

The findings are supported by another recent study from Israel.

(Note that the findings are also supported by innumerable scientists and physicians who were summarily dismissed (and more) for suggesting that this was likely early in the pandemic.)

Source: The Epoch Times; NEJM; AFLDS

“Indonesian official charged, but not jailed, for trading in Sumatran tiger parts”⁠
⁠
The Aceh province, at the northern tip of Sumatra, is believed to hold about 200 of the world’s remaining 400 Sumatran tigers — the last tiger endemic to Indonesia following the extinction in the last century of the Bali and Javan subspecies. Sumatran tigers are protected under Indonesia’s Conservation Act. Illegal capture, distribution, and trade of any protected species or its parts are punishable by up to five years in prison and extensive fines.⁠
⁠
Ahmadi, the former head of Bener Meriah district in Aceh province, was arrested on May 24 by police along with two alleged accomplices while transacting a sale for the hide and bones of a Sumatran tiger. However, @Mongabay reports he was released shortly after without any charges.⁠
⁠
This kind of treatment is emblematic of one of the root problems in addressing wildlife trafficking around the world- the fact that the perpetrators tend to be influential figures such as politicians, government officials, and military officers, who utilize their positions of power to enjoy impunity when engaging in illicit activities.⁠
⁠
Within our work, ELI has discovered ample evidence of the link between environmental crime and corruption. In our operations, ELI has uncovered some element of corruption in every single wildlife trafficking network we target. Thus, ELI’s investigative work is critical in exposing and addressing the layer of corruption that underlies wildlife crime. Without ELI’s work, corruption will continue to go undetected and wildlife will remain defenseless to its impacts. ⁠
⁠

"WESTERN MEDIA" BEFORE AND AFTER THE WAR IN UKRAINE (read description for context). 

This post isn't about Ukraine or these specific articles, but about the media and specifically the western one. And I'm not implying that before the war these western articles told the truth and after only lies. Not at all. This post isn't about that. 

However, this image is for the average western viewer of the traditional news media that believes it almost blindly and thinks that we have "an independent media". Of course our situation is not as bad as in some other countries in terms of freedom of the press, but we have huge problems of corruption, and political and let's face it, private interests influencing and directly conditioning the media sector.

Again, this post isn't about saying that the New Europe article about Zelensky from 2021 is true but the one from The Washington Post from 2022 isn't... Every article has to be analyzed and fact-checked personally by the one reading it. It's the time we are living in. When you can't trust the media, even in the west...

Cause if you trust it, you end up trying to explain to yourself how Ukraine is the full-on democracy fighting for liberal ideas two days after you though that it was the most corrupt and authoritarian country in Europe...

"Thankfully" our society has a very short memory so our public opinion is modeled perfectly to the needs of the big corporations (be it the military industrial complex, or the pharmaceutical) and corrupt or just greedy politicians.

I know it's almost a topic to say that our media is influenced by these private and public interests, but we seem to not care at all, and every year the situation gets only worse in my opinion.

Give this post a like if it made you think or if you, you know... simply liked it.

Sources: the articles in the post are all public articles that you can search and read in two clicks. The articles from before the war range from the year 2015 - 2021.

Civil rights advocacy group, Human Rights Writers Association of Nigeria, has called on the National Judicial Council and the Code of Conduct Tribunal to probe the corruption allegations levelled against the Chief Justice of Nigeria, Tanko Muhammad, serving justices of the Supreme Court.

In a statement signed by the group’s National Coordinator, Comrade Emmanuel Onwubiko, on Wednesday, HURIWA stated that the CJN should step down as Chairman of the NJC for the investigation to be conducted.

The group noted that the failure of the NJC and the CCT to investigate the allegations against Muhammad was tantamount to injustice considering the fact that the former CJN, Walter Onnoghen, was removed on a controversial note following allegations against him which were probed by both the NJC and the CCT.

The PUNCH had reported that Justices of the Supreme Court had, in a joint petition, accused the CJN of corruption, maladministration and incompetence.
